## v4.0.0 (2026-04-06)

**Changed by:** Session — Fifth review pass with myrmidon swarm (Opus 4.6, 1M context)
**Verification:** verified-local (pixi run paper-build, clean)

### What changed
- Bumped version from 3.1.0 to 4.0.0
- Added Step 2c (Myrmidon swarm independent verification) to Verified Workflow
- Added 5 new error patterns: Pattern 21 (grading scale paper-vs-code mismatch), Pattern 22 (pass classification majority vote vs threshold), Pattern 23 (Cliff's delta FAIR vs journal convention), Pattern 24 (judge agreement N on pivoted data), Pattern 25 (column specifier off-by-one is systematic)
- Added myrmidon swarm composition and role-based instructions in Step 2c
- Added "When to Use" triggers for grading scales, myrmidon swarm review, pivoted data N-values
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows (Haiku student CoP and consistency false positives)
- Added v4.0.0 session outcome to Results & Parameters
- Added v4.0.0 row to Verified On table
- Extended Key Source Files table with grading scale, judge agreement analysis, table generation entries
- Added tags: grading-scale, majority-vote, cliffs-delta, myrmidon-swarm

### Why
Fifth review pass of `docs/arxiv/haiku/paper.tex`. After 4 prior review rounds, deployed a myrmidon swarm (2 Sonnet professors + 3 Haiku students) for independent multi-perspective review. Found grading scale paper-vs-code mismatch (864/1080 rows matched paper scale, 1080/1080 matched code scale), pass classification mechanism wrong (majority vote vs threshold, 16 mismatches prove difference), Cliff's delta FAIR vs journal threshold convention, judge agreement N-value on pivoted data (360 vs 2,696), and recurring column specifier off-by-one in additional tables.

