## v3.0.0 (2026-04-06)

**Changed by:** Session — N=3 experiment data refresh and academic review (third pass)
**Verification:** verified-local (tectonic builds paper to 50-page 978KB PDF)

### What changed
- Bumped version from 2.0.0 to 3.0.0, updated date to 2026-04-06
- Added Step 2b (Independent CI verification) to Verified Workflow
- Added 4 new error patterns: Pattern 15 (bootstrap CIs mislabeled as Clopper-Pearson), Pattern 16 (missing judge evaluations), Pattern 17 (BH monotonicity comment errors), Pattern 18 (consensus method description errors)
- Updated Overview outcome to include v3.0.0 findings
- Added 2 new "When to Use" triggers for CI verification and missing judge evaluations
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows (trusting CI labels, assuming complete evaluations)
- Added v3.0.0 session outcome to Results & Parameters
- Added v3.0.0 row to Verified On table
- Extended Key Source Files table with pass threshold, bootstrap config, and subtest YAML counts
- Added tags: confidence-intervals, iftex

### Why
Third review pass of `docs/arxiv/haiku/paper.tex` after N=3 experiment data refresh.
Discovered that bootstrap CIs were mislabeled as Clopper-Pearson throughout the paper
(critical), 536 missing judge evaluations in test-001 were undisclosed (critical),
BH monotonicity enforcement comments in analysis code were incorrect (important),
and consensus method was described as "majority vote" but implemented as mean
thresholding (important).

